  <h2>The Discipline is:</h2>
  <p>an <span class="def" id="expulsion">expulsion*</span>.</p>
</div>
  <h2>Response:</h2>
  <p>School  administrators must give you written notification of the intent to  expel your child. In the case of a proposed expulsion, you are entitled to  written notice that contains a complete statement of the facts, a list of  witnesses and a description of their testimony, as well as many other  procedural rights under the Minnesota Pupil Fair Dismissal Act.<sup class="statute">1</sup></p>
  <p>A  <span class="def" id="manifestation-determination">manifestation determination*</span> meeting must then be held by a group of persons  knowledgeable about your child, the meaning of the 504 evaluation data, and the  placement options to decide whether your childâ€™s behavior was caused by or had  a direct and substantial relationship to his or her disability. </p>
  <p>If  the behavior in question was drug or alcohol use, the school can suspend or  expel your child, just as it would a student without a disability. For behavior  involving drug or alcohol use, a manifestation meeting is not required.</p>
